_0058.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" type="image/webp">


<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LPiwuxUfhadSc79TjyxM0d44mqg=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SRY-FxbFgAExNs9HnwNkthK5hTU=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_T6q2C7A0FJSl4yJ3K1-U2nkBRU=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4NXwhhTGEoY6dMsH6BuifRTldTY=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PcBEHVTUokTYXLzvjDDnQI-IeLQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Njsz9efUQBSd41bcNcQE62K4Zis=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wA0pwTKEPYSnP-elfrOlJbBiiJg=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ybG3HgVF7K0FIt0nKiKDxgOHpSU=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3UPf0qyk4Z2DwVi3rmoVQmiPsRA=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2040" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Fu7y2W7OAnIO_ir634KNWl2ZdT0=/0x0:2040x1360/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19895599/vpavic_042009_3967_0058.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
</figure>

</div>
</div></div>
<p id="DOxZXn">While we’re talking about looks, we should probably recap the color options for the OnePlus 8. If you’re buying unlocked in the US, you can get the phone in green or a multicolored finish OnePlus is calling “interstellar glow.” You get green if you go for the model with 8GB of RAM, and you get interstellar glow if you opt for 12GB. Meanwhile, in the UK, you can get the handset in a matte green or glossy black. You get green if you go for 12GB of RAM and black with 8GB. I’ve only had a chance to see the green model in person, and while I appreciate a matte finish for its resistance to fingerprints and other smudges, I don’t love the exact shade of green.</p>
<p id="1JIeTv">The OnePlus 8 has a 6.55-inch 20:9 1080p display with a maximum refresh rate of 90Hz and a maximum brightness of 1100 nits. If you’re doing a numbers-to-numbers comparison, that’s technically a step down from the 6.78-inch, 1440p, 120Hz, 1300-nit display in the 8 Pro. But I found any tangible differences to be minor. By any measure, the OnePlus 8 has a great display. It’s bright, vibrant, and buttery smooth. It also doesn’t curve around the edges of the phone quite as much as the screen on the 8 Pro, which could explain why I didn’t have the same problems with accidental touches that Dieter experienced.</p>
<div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"><aside id="AhAUnV"><q>It’s a great display by any measure</q></aside></div>
<p id="qZrOwK">Maybe there’ll come a point when we’re all so used to 90Hz displays that the difference between 90 and 120Hz will feel as significant as the difference between 60 and 90Hz, but I’m not there yet. I had to sit both phones side by side to see the difference. Even then, I don’t think it’s night and day. The takeaway is that you’re not getting a compromised display on the OnePlus 8.</p>
