<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AEFSufKX_rB5NkaNqzVUSnTSGos=/0x0:2448x3264/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fv-LmzdH3_DIJrWIRHjQsptjQb8=/0x0:2448x3264/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O0TtJR7W6lIbOFdDgPBpfjVUuBk=/0x0:2448x3264/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OnpKBROJk--2sDwzm78vtzfgC2s=/0x0:2448x3264/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iCbKUulWQoPCS0lB8HyKxxjcwVg=/0x0:2448x3264/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eMt4x2W-3owJVdlnEyUaeYVx2ko=/0x0:2448x3264/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_oSo0w-4O1bsPCKR6b1jU-4osMs=/0x0:2448x3264/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/B87o39KsO3o3A95tF3CehvILf3g=/0x0:2448x3264/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NeF3bg58QiSAlFwdmk94QU86WiY=/0x0:2448x3264/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2448" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1qjpn82dgYckSopyWSBE_JsMNdQ=/0x0:2448x3264/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2448x3264):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19898094/MVIMG_20200407_160139.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
        <figcaption><em>Pixel 3.</em></figcaption>
      
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

</div>
</div></div>
<p id="l4Av7D">As mentioned, there’s a low-resolution macro camera in the rear camera array on the OnePlus 8, but I found it to be of limited use. Some shots in good light turn out better, but other times, I actually got a better shot out of the 8 Pro because of its superior main sensor.</p>
<p id="ph2767">Suffice it to say, if you want a zoom lens and a better-quality camera overall, particularly when it comes to low-light performance, then you have to go for the 8 Pro. The more difficult question is whether the OnePlus 8’s camera holds up against its similarly priced competitors like the entry-level iPhone 11, and I don’t think it quite nails it.</p>
<div class="c-float-right c-float-hang"><aside id="R9QxhQ"><q>$200 more gets you wireless charging and an IP rating</q></aside></div>
<p id="Yl57F0">So that’s the OnePlus 8. It has all of the things you can expect from a OnePlus device, and I mean that in both good and bad ways. It’s got a great screen, great performance, great battery life, its camera could stand to be a little better, and for reasons that seem to apply only to OnePlus, the unlocked versions aren’t IP-rated and none of them do wireless charging. There’s a OnePlus mold, and the OnePlus 8 has chosen not to break it. </p>
<p class="c-end-para" id="vY8aeg">So the big question if you want to buy a OnePlus device is whether a $200 price premium is worth it for a slightly better camera, an IP rating, and wireless charging. If it’s not, then the OnePlus 8 is a great option.</p>
<p id="baAKHB"><small><em>Vox Media has affiliate partnerships. These do not influence editorial content, though Vox Media may earn commissions for products purchased via affiliate links. For more information, see </em></small><a href="https://www.theverge.com/ethics-statement"><small><em>our ethics policy</em></small></a><small><em>.</em></small></p>
<p id="QigOId"><em><strong>Update March 14th, 1:03PM ET:</strong></em><em> Updated with OnePlus’s confirmation that the carrier versions of the OnePlus 8 will have an IP68 water resistance rating. </em></p>
